This paper discusses the consensus mechanism of the DFINITY blockchain computer, which involves a decentralized randomness beacon and a threshold signatures scheme. This topic is closely related to cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of weight and notarization to improve the blockchain's security, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG) respectively.
